It's  the age old story of friends falling in love and for whatever reason one party never knows until they are about to lose thier friend forever. No matter how many times I see or read such a story it never gets old.  I did find it wierd the Kiesha and Romeo were supposed to be the same age when there is like a 15 year or more age gap in between the two. It didn't  take away from the story itnjust made me want to watch to see how that would come across on screen, you know would it be believable and you know what.... it was. I guess  that is the strength  of being good actors.
